HEADWORD: Sorb
<hw>Sorb</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[L. <ets>sorbus the
tree</ets>, <ets>sorbum</ets> the fruit; cf. F. <ets>sorbe</ets>. See
<er>Service tree</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
wild service tree (<spn>Pyrus torminalis</spn>) of Europe; also, the
rowan tree.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The fruit of these trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sorb apple</b></col>, <cd>the fruit of the sorb, or wild
service tree.</cd> -- <col><b>Sorb tree</b></col>, <cd>the wild service
tree.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorbate</ent>⟦br⟧
